CFNotificationCenterPostNotification(center, name, nil, nil, true)`})}),o.jsx("p",{children:"If the App is open, it hears this shout, immediately opens the locker, and refreshes the list using a reactive SwiftData query. This happens so fast that it feels like the item teleported from one app to the other."}),o.jsx("h3",{children:"Asymmetric Synchrony"}),o.jsx("p",{children:"I built the App and the Keyboard with different rhythms to balance speed with battery efficiency."}),o.jsxs("ul",{children:[o.jsxs("li",{children:[o.jsx("strong",{children:"The Keyboard is Paranoid:"})," It only lives for the few seconds you are actually typing, so it pulses every 0.5 seconds. It also runs a high-speed check the literal millisecond it starts to slide up. This ensures that even if you just copied something in Safari, it is already rendered at the top of the history before the keyboard is fully visible."]}),o.jsxs("li",{children:[o.jsx("strong",{children:"The App is Passive:"})," It stays in memory much longer and wants to save your battery. It pulses every 2.0 seconds. It doesn't need to be faster because it knows if anything urgent happens, the Keyboard will use the megaphone to wake it up."]})]}),o.jsx("pre",{children:o.jsx("code",{children:`// Example of the Keyboard's 0.5s Monitor
